Bruce Martin
31 August 2020

This reading covers change enablement within the ITIL framework.

"The purpose of the change enablement practice is to maximize the number of successful IT changes by ensuring that risks have haven assessed,
authorizing changes to proceed, and managing the change schedule."

There are 3 change types: Standard, Normal and Emergency.  Each have clearly defined parameters that differentiates them from each other.

Change authority is the person in the organization who authorizes change.

Communication is vital across the organization.

There are 6 parts of the service value chain:  Plan, Engage, Design & Transition, Obtain/Build, Deliver & Support and Improve
